06965674-128a-42ba-8ff4-1f72c6a4962f,I011,Yalla Return,ACTIVE,AEPW,United Arab Emirates,UAE,PUBLISHED,"The Yalla Return project aims to increase collection of plastic waste in public and residential areas in Abu Dhabi and Dubai. The platform engages the public through an application that offers awareness and guidance on types of plastic waste to be sorted and recycled, which eventually reflect on user’s dashboard to measure the impact of individuals and deposit incentives into user’s accounts. The Yalla Return platform is a private start-up initiated during 2021 started in Lebanon and UAE, and gained recognition in several events such as winning the LEAP start-up awards and the PepsiCo Accelerator. The platform has reached more than 15,000 users and executed more than 100,000 transactions. 
· The project aims to boost Yalla Return platform operations through investing in new CAPEX that contribute in expanding community size and securing access to collect additional volume of recyclables of 0.6 KTA.
· Increase consumer awareness about the value of plastic recyclables and encourage manufacturers to use recyclables in their production.
· The solution model aligns with UAE Circular Economy Policy and contribute to three Alliance Impact Metrics: Reduce Unmanaged Waste, Capture Value from Waste, and Create Social Benefit.
Approach:
· Deployment of additional 17 smart bins in 10 vertical communities and 7 retailers in Dubai and Abu Dhabi, linked by a traceable system through scanning QR codes on bags and smart bins integrated with Yalla Return's digital application.
· Extend operations to additional 10 horizontal residential communities within Dubai through rebranding door to door bins, collecting recyclables from houses, and distributing recycling kits to the residents.
· Conduct awareness and promotion campaigns to engage with the public and develop “at source” segregation habits.
· The project estimates adding around 8,000 new users from 27 new communities and attract new sponsors and partners.","Yalla Return, which means """"Let's Go Return"""" in Arabic/English, is a digital platform and collection bin network that supports the recovery of recyclables by encouraging consumers and businesses to sort their waste and recycle.",,,"[""24.46899771458840800"",""54.38414167166690000""]",ESTIMATE,,,,2024-10-29 09:28:34.98
2058667c-24f1-427a-99fc-e6df69511639,L091,COtooClean,ACTIVE,AEPW,United Kingdom,Europe,DRAFT,"COtooCLEAN is a waterless cleaning process for polyolefin (PE/PP) films, based on low-pressure super-critical CO2. This provides a potential solution for mechanically recycling of polyolefin films to food-contact under FDA and European Food Safety approval. Nextek intends to demonstrate the solution's technical and economic performance through a pilot facility utilizing AEPW's prize money of . In 2023, the focus has been on developing the project scope and identifying partner(s). The project group consists of Nextek Ltd (tech owner), Unilever (supply films and testing), Amcor (PCR incorporation), Allied Mills (supply printed films for de-inking and testing), Suprex (equipment design and construction), University of Nottingham (optimization study on co-solvents for de-inking) and Bangor University (LCA and process optimization). The COtooCLEAN plant will be developed between Nextek and a to-be-identified partner. This partner will contribute in one or more of the following: the site and building, input materials and market for the end-product.","Innovative technology of dry de-contamination of polyolefin films to achieve food-grade certification through mechanical recycling; future possibility to replace hotwash, deinking and deodorization steps.",,Nextek/COtooClean Ltd,"[""51.50163800163403500"",""-0.17520879009303160""]",ESTIMATE,"Country changed to London, United Kingdom from ""Austria; Belgium; Denmark; Finland; France; Germany; Italy; Netherlands",,,2024-10-29 09:28:34.98
